&lt;h2 id=&#34;hi-i-m-andrew&#34;&gt;Hi, I&amp;rsquo;m Andrew&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m an Android Developer who has recently &lt;a href=&#34;http://andrewemerson.io/post/starting-my-career-change/&#34;&gt;switched careers&lt;/a&gt; from IT Consulting and I&amp;rsquo;m loving it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&amp;rsquo;t want to rehash my CV here. For that, you can &lt;a href=&#34;http://andrewemerson.io/CV/Andrew_Emerson-Android_Engineer-CV.pdf&#34;&gt;download it&lt;/a&gt;, take a look at my StackOverflow &lt;a href=&#34;https://stackoverflow.com/story/aoemerson&#34;&gt;developer story&lt;/a&gt;, browse &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/aoemerson&#34;&gt;my github&lt;/a&gt; or try any one of other social links in the header up above.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-makes-me-tech&#34;&gt;What makes me Tech&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The technology products that excite me the most are those that have the greatest impact on simplifying the lives of the individual. I&amp;rsquo;m less about &lt;strong&gt;staring&lt;/strong&gt; at your smartphone for hours on end and more about it being a trusted companion that&amp;rsquo;s reliably there when you need it but won&amp;rsquo;t betray you when you&amp;rsquo;re not looking.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maps. I also really like apps that utilise maps. I&amp;rsquo;ve even started having a go at &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/aoemerson/crimes-app&#34;&gt;making one&lt;/a&gt; and I intend to blog about some of the interesting challenges raised when making apps with maps.&lt;/p&gt;

